    <div class="bg-accent/5 border border-accent/20 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">The bottom line</h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed m-0">
        The Fable 5 episode was not a failure of values — it was a failure of <em>process built on facts</em>. The United States can have the EU AI Act's predictability without its licensing regime, because the structure that makes governance fair is an evidence layer, and that layer can be open infrastructure. RCAN specifies it for embodied AI; the Robot Registry Foundation anchors it. The work is already shipping — what remains is for policy to point at it.
      </p>
